ts of functions do such identities serve? What political ideals does Nietzsche advocate? What conceptual tools for reanimating liberatory political projects does Nietzsche promote? How might we organize politically to affirm life and acknowledge the tragic as we avoid the pull of nihilism? The essays within this volume engage these questions and offer fresh, at times surprising, answers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aIdentity (Philosophical concept). 0aIdentity politics. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Essays.2bisacsh1 aBamford, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBamford, Rebecca, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aConway, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCreasy, Kaitlyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFortier, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuay, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatab, Lawrence J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirkland, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLongtin, Rebecca A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMerrick, Allison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMerrick, Allison, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPloof, Rebecca Aili, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchotten, C. Heike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScott, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/re